## What We Are Building

A self-update system for the `gchat` CLI (the `group-chat-mcp` npm package). Two capabilities:

1. Passive update notice: after interactive commands (`install`, `uninstall`), the CLI checks the npm registry in parallel and prints an update notice if a newer version exists. Cached for 24 hours.

2. Manual update command: `gchat update` runs `npm install -g group-chat-mcp@latest`, then re-execs the newly installed binary with `gchat update --post-install` so the new version's installer logic refreshes all IDE configs. Install metadata (`~/.group-chat-mcp/install-meta.json`) tracks which IDE+scope combos were configured so the post-install knows what to refresh.

Key design decisions: no auto-update, no version pinning, no interactive prompts, no notice on hook commands (cursor-join/cursor-leave output JSON), re-exec new binary for config refresh.

