## Decisions Made

- **Notify only, no auto-update** — reason: mutating global state without consent is risky; user must explicitly run `gchat update`
- **Interactive commands only for notice** — reason: hook commands (cursor-join, cursor-leave) output JSON to stdout; any extra output corrupts parsing
- **24h cache for version check** — reason: avoids repeated npm registry calls; eliminates latency on consecutive runs
- **Latest version only, no pinning** — reason: simplicity; covers 99% of use cases
- **Persist install metadata in ~/.group-chat-mcp/install-meta.json** — reason: reliable detection of what to refresh; no fragile config scanning
- **Re-exec new binary after npm install** — reason: running process has old code loaded; new binary must apply its own installer logic for config correctness
- **Parallel version check, print after** — reason: no added latency to the primary command; standard CLI pattern (npm, Angular CLI)
- **No full reinstall on update** — reason: the installer's merge logic is idempotent; re-applying it refreshes configs without clobbering unrelated settings

